An all-star cast portrays this most mysterious and poignant event of the First World War - the disappearance in action of the Sandringham Company at Gallipoli in 1915. Commanded by the Estate Manager, Captain Frank Beck (David Jason), they were just ordinary men - servants, grooms and gardeners - drawn from the staff of the King&#8217;s private residence. They left an idyllic rural existence for the fatally ill-prepared campaign and their deaths brought the horrors of the First World War to the heart of the establishment - and to the Royal Family itself. After the war a Special Envoy was sent at the behest of Queen Alexandra (Maggie Smith) to discover what fate had befallen the Company. But the truth was never fully revealed&#8230; Also includes a documentary &#8220;All the kings men&#8221;, produced in 1991 and presented by HRH The Prince Edward.</p>", "constellations_primary": [], "constellations_other": [], "recommendations": [], "creator_credit_for_label": "<p>Julian Jarrold, Gareth Neame, BBC-TV and WGBH (Boston)</p>", "creator_credit_for_label_zh_hans": "", "creator_credit_for_label_pa": "", "creator_credit_for_label_hi": "", "headline_credit_for_label": "<p>United Kingdom, 1999</p>", "headline_credit_for_label_zh_hans": "", "headline_credit_for_label_pa": "", "headline_credit_for_label_hi": "", "title_for_label_zh_hans": "", "title_for_label_pa": "", "title_for_label_hi": "", "title_for_label_override_zh_hans": "", "title_for_label_override_pa": "", "title_for_label_override_hi": "", "description_for_label_zh_hans": "", "description_for_label_pa": "", "description_for_label_hi": "", "description_for_label_override_zh_hans": "", "description_for_label_override_pa": "", "description_for_label_override_hi": "", "description_zh_hans": "", "description_pa": "", "description_hi": "", "description_override_zh_hans": "", "description_override_pa": "", "description_override_hi": "", "title_for_label": "<p>All the king&#8217;s men</p>", "description": "<p>An all-star c